Comment: I start with the king's pawn opening like I always do.
I've never done that.
I will bring my other pawn out
She brings queens pawn out protected by his king pawn.
I develop my knight.
She brings his queen out. I have no idea why.
I take his pawn.
She takes my pawn back.
I develop my bishop pinning his queen.
She blocks it with her pawn.
I bring my bishop back.
She goes looking for a queen trade.
I take because its still tied.
She takes back with his bishop.
I develop my knight.
She develops hers.
I attack his queen-taking rook.
She backs his bishop away.
I finally castle.
She moves her rook to d8. I have know idea why.
